{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"3802","heading":"False claims and statements; liability","label":"3802 False claims and statements; liability","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/stIII/ch38","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2024—Subsec. (a)(3). designated existing provisions as subpar. (A), substituted “Except as provided in subparagraph (B), an assessment” for “An assessment”, and added subpar. (B).Pub. L. 118–159"],"amendments":["Amendments2024—Subsec. (a)(3). designated existing provisions as subpar. (A), substituted “Except as provided in subparagraph (B), an assessment” for “An assessment”, and added subpar. (B).Pub. L. 118–159"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":null,"label":"a","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is false, fictitious, or fraudulent;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"includes or is supported by any written statement which asserts a material fact which is false, fictitious, or fraudulent;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FC%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"omits a material fact;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FC%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is false, fictitious, or fraudulent as a result of such omission; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"iii","heading":null,"label":"iii","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C/iii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/C","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FC%2Fiii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is a statement in which the person making, presenting, or submitting such statement has a duty to include such material fact; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"D","heading":null,"label":"D","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1/D","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F1%2FD","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is for payment for the provision of property or services which the person has not provided as claimed,","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"i","heading":null,"label":"i","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A/i","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FA%2Fi","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"asserts a material fact which is false, fictitious, or fraudulent; or","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"clause","nativeType":"clause","number":"ii","heading":null,"label":"ii","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A/ii","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FA%2Fii","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"I","heading":null,"label":"I","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A/ii/I","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FA%2Fii%2FI","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"omits a material fact; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subclause","nativeType":"subclause","number":"II","heading":null,"label":"II","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A/ii/II","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/A/ii","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FA%2Fii%2FII","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"is false, fictitious, or fraudulent as a result of such omission;","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"in the case of a statement described in clause (ii) of subparagraph (A), is a statement in which the person making, presenting, or submitting such statement has a duty to include such material fact; and","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"C","heading":null,"label":"C","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2/C","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/2","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F2%2FC","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"contains or is accompanied by an express certification or affirmation of the truthfulness and accuracy of the contents of the statement,","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/3/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F3%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"Except as provided in subparagraph (B), an assessment shall not be made under the second sentence of paragraph (1) with respect to a claim if payment by the Government has not been made on such claim.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/3/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/a/3","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fa%2F3%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In the case of a claim described in section 3801(a)(3)(C), an assessment shall not be made under the second sentence of paragraph (1) in an amount that is more than double the value of the property, services, or money that was wrongfully withheld from the authority.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":null,"label":"b","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"1","heading":null,"label":"1","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/1","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fb%2F1","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"A","heading":null,"label":"A","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/1/A","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fb%2F1%2FA","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a determination under that there is adequate evidence to believe that a person is liable under subsection (a) of this section; orsection 3803(a)(2) of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subparagraph","nativeType":"subparagraph","number":"B","heading":null,"label":"B","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/1/B","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/1","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fb%2F1%2FB","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"a determination under that a person is liable under subsection (a) of this section,section 3803 of this title","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"2","heading":null,"label":"2","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/2","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fb%2F2","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"A determination referred to in paragraph (1) of this subsection may be used by the authority, but shall not require such authority, to commence any administrative or contractual action which is authorized by law.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"paragraph","nativeType":"paragraph","number":"3","heading":null,"label":"3","identifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b/3","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t31/s3802/b","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft31%2Fs3802%2Fb%2F3","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"In the case of an administrative or contractual action to suspend or debar any person who is eligible to enter into contracts with the Federal Government, a determination referred to in paragraph (1) of this subsection shall not be considered as a conclusive determination of such person’s responsibility pursuant to Federal procurement laws and regulations.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]}]}]}
